&lt;p&gt;Arevon is recruiting for the position of &lt;strong&gt;Senior&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Analyst, Performance Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;, &lt;/em&gt;an outstanding opportunity for individuals seeking an exciting, high-growth work environment in one of the most important industries for the 21st century. Our company culture is one where teamwork, adaptability, continuous improvement, achievement of results, and willingness to grow are our core values. The successful candidate will have a superior professional background at a high caliber institution, having exceeded in &lt;strong&gt;Engineering or a Mathematical Science Discipline &lt;/strong&gt;and multiple years of work experience&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;in Data Engineering and Data Science roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maximizing performance of assets through building and developing tools and products that determine overall health of solar and battery storage assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use existing tools to develop, implement, and improve methods for detecting, reporting, and analyzing performance issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the implementation of monitoring software to capture project data and perform detailed analysis for solar and BESS KPIs and monthly reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep abreast of the latest PVsyst and performance modelling developments, develop new methods/tools as appropriate, and train team members on any new procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategies to optimize performance of renewable assets and identify areas of underperformance, drive improvements and corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Project Development team with inverter, battery, transformer and tracker/racking. technologies in support of equipment selection and procurement and build a team to support the reliability analysis of various components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with the Operations Engineering team on revenue impacting underperformance events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously evaluate software systems, processes, procedures and drive improvement within the performance and operational engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with internal and external engineering and construction teams on project substantial completion testing and verifying or running capacity tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aide in the technical due-diligence process for potential acquisitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review technical documents and acceptance test during the project handover process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
